  "texts": [
    "• Precision: Measures the accuracy of predicted spam emails among all emails classified as spam.",
    "It is calculated as: Precision = True Positives True Positives + False Positives, where False Positives (FP) are legitimate emails incorrectly classified as spam.",
    "• Recall: The proportion of actual spam emails correctly identified, also known as Sensitivity.",
    "It is given by: Recall = True Positives True Positives + False Negatives, where False Negatives (FN) are spam emails incorrectly classified as legitimate.TABLE II: Evaluation Metrics Results for ChatGPT-4 Metric Value Accuracy 0.94 Precision 0.92 Recall 0.93 F1-Score 0.925• F1-Score: The harmonic mean of precision and recall, providing a single measure of model performance, especially in cases where precision and recall might diverge.It is defined as:F 1-Score = 2 • Precision • Recall Precision + Recall.These metrics collectively offer a sophisticated view of model performance, highlighting strengths and weaknesses in spam detection capabilities.",
    "Accuracy provides a general sense of overall performance, while precision and recall focus on the model's effectiveness in identifying spam specifically."
